<h1>Directory of Lefthanders Resources</h1>

    <p>
        <a href="/">Home</a> >
            <a href="/Society">Society</a>  >             <a href="/Society/People">People</a>  >             <a href="/Society/People/Lefthanders">Lefthanders</a>         </p>

<p><p>About being left-handed, people who are left-handed, and handedness in general. Sites offering products designed for use by the left-handed are listed in <a href="/Shopping/Niche/Left-Handed_Products/">Shopping/Niche/Left-Handed_Products/</a>.</p></p>

<h2>Subcategories</h2>
<ul id="triple">
    <li><a href="/Sports/Golf/Organizations/Associations_and_Leagues/Lefties" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left-Handed Golf Organizations</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="/Shopping/Niche/Left-Handed_Products" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left-Handed Products</strong></a></li>
</ul>
<div style="clear:both"></div>

<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.faqs.org/faqs/lefty-faq/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Alt.lefthanders Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.faqs.org/faqs/lefty-faq/</strong></font> <br /> Usenet FAQ. Includes questions such as: What does being &quot;left-handed&quot; or &quot;ambidextrous&quot; mean? Is lefthandedness inherited? Are lefthanders naturally clumsy? Do Lefties make better athletes?</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.clas.co.uk/left-handers.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Calligraphy and Lettering Arts Society</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.clas.co.uk/left-handers.html</strong></font> <br /> &quot;If you are left handed, do not despair.&quot; Advice for left-handers who want to learn calligraphy.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.hcs.harvard.edu/~hsmbb/BRAIN/vol2/left.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Creation of the Sinister: Biological Contributions to Left-handedness</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.hcs.harvard.edu/~hsmbb/BRAIN/vol2/left.html</strong></font> <br /> Critique of the Geschwind-Behan-Galaburda (GBG) Theory of Left-Handedness and other theories that associate lefthandedness with developmental disorders. Published in the Harvard undergraduate neuroscience journal, Brain.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.crochet.org/?page=StitchesLeftHand" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Crochet Lessons for Left-Handers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.crochet.org/?page=StitchesLeftHand</strong></font> <br /> Instructions, with helpful diagrams.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/left.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Famous Left-Handers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/left.html</strong></font> <br /> Long list of left-handed actors, artists, authors, musicians, athletes, politicians, U.S. presidents, and historical figures.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.gaskellguitars.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Gaskell Guitars</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.gaskellguitars.com/</strong></font> <br /> Australian company that makes only left hand guitars of models not available in left hand option by original manufacturers. Model photos and descriptions, where to buy, and other details.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/lspeak.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Gauche! Left-Handers in Society</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/lspeak.html</strong></font> <br /> A resource guide and forum. Left-handers speak to parents, teachers, employers, physicians, and others.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.handedness.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Handedness Research Institute</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.handedness.org/</strong></font> <br /> Advances the scientific understanding of handedness (left-handed, right-handed and mixed manual preferences) and helps alleviate the social and educational discrimination of left-handers worldwide through research and education.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/plat20/current" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Laterality: Asymmetries of Body, Brain and Cognition</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/plat20/current</strong></font> <br /> Scientific journal publishing research on the psychological, behavioural and neurological aspects of lateralisation, including handedness. Online tables of contents, abstracts, instructions to authors, and other information.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.lefthandersday.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left Handers Day</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.lefthandersday.com/</strong></font> <br /> Left Handers Day is on 13 August. Information about handedness, fun facts, games and quizzes.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.left-is-right.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left Is Right</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.left-is-right.com/</strong></font> <br /> Promotes a book described as a survival guide for living lefty in a right-handed world. Includes some information about handedness and famous lefties.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.nibs.com/Left-hand%20writers.htm" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left-Handed Writers Page</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.nibs.com/Left-hand%20writers.htm</strong></font> <br /> Article about left-handed writing with fountain pens, including advice on nib selection. Photographs show different hand positions lefties write in, with special advice for each.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.islamicity.com/dialogue/Q325.HTM" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left-handedness</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.islamicity.com/dialogue/Q325.HTM</strong></font> <br /> A modern Islamic perspective on being left-handed.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://lefthand.webstarts.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Left-handers Club of Ireland</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://lefthand.webstarts.com/</strong></font> <br /> Short newsletter, products for sale, and other information.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.members.shaw.ca/leftovers/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>LEFTovers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.members.shaw.ca/leftovers/</strong></font> <br /> List of lefthanded Canadians. Also contains left-handed stores in Canada.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://faculty.washington.edu/chudler/rightl.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Neuroscience for Kids - Sidedness</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://faculty.washington.edu/chudler/rightl.html</strong></font> <br /> Educational website about laterality. Includes tests for handedness, footedness, eyedness, and earedness.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/index.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Primate Handedness and Brain Lateralization Research</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.indiana.edu/~primate/index.html</strong></font> <br /> At Indiana University (M.K. Holder, Ph.D.). You can participate in the study by filling out an online questionnaire. Site also has links to information (both serious and fun) of interest to left-handers.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.righthandlefthand.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Right Hand, Left Hand</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.righthandlefthand.com/</strong></font> <br /> Website for Chris McManus&#039; book on handedness. Includes articles and online psychological quizzes.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.left-hand.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Rosemary West's Left-Handed Page</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.left-hand.org/</strong></font> <br /> Large collection of information and links, including organizations, research articles, list of famous left-handers, left-handedness in the arts, links to shopping sites, FAQ, humor, fun facts, and trivia.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/what-causes-some-people-t/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Scientific American: Ask the Experts: Biology</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/what-causes-some-people-t/</strong></font> <br /> M.K. Holder answers the questions: &quot;Do scientists understand why there are so many more right-handers than left-handers? Do other primates show a similar tendency to favor one hand over the other?&quot;</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.dpjs.co.uk/lefthandpath.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Left Hand Path</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.dpjs.co.uk/lefthandpath.html</strong></font> <br /> Speculations on how left-handedness came to be associated with satanism in western mythology.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.zaner-bloser.com/news/left-handed-child-right-handed-world" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Left-Handed Child in a Right-Handed World</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.zaner-bloser.com/news/left-handed-child-right-handed-world</strong></font> <br /> Advice on determining hand dominance and on dealing with handwriting problems often encountered in left-handers.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.lefthander.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Lefthanded Liberation Front</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.lefthander.com/</strong></font> <br /> Site has webforum, merchandise for sale, humor, and other material.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://riksmits.home.xs4all.nl/lhu/lhu.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Lefthanded Universe</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://riksmits.home.xs4all.nl/lhu/lhu.html</strong></font> <br /> Interesting facts and ideas about lefthandedness. [English, Dutch, German]</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://web-japan.org/trends00/honbun/tj000202.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Trends in Japan: Rise Up, Ye Southpaws</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://web-japan.org/trends00/honbun/tj000202.html</strong></font> <br /> Article discusses the increased acceptance of lefthandedness in Japan.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/uk/2002/jun/06/research.medicalscience" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Why Left-handers Still Feel Left Out</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.theguardian.com/uk/2002/jun/06/research.medicalscience</strong></font> <br /> Guardian article describes researcher&#039;s finding that left-handed people have been abused and neglected throughout history.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>


